5000|$|Tetrasodium pyro{{phosphate}}, {{also called}} sodium pyrophosphate, tetrasodium phosphate or TSPP, is a colorless transparent crystalline chemical compound with the formula <b>Na4P2O7.</b> It is a salt composed of pyrophosphate and sodium ions. Toxicity is approximately {{twice that of}} table salt when ingested orally. [...] There is also a hydrated form, Na4P2O710(H2O).|$|E

